<div class="space-y-6">
  <% content_for :page_header do %>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3">
      <div>
        <h2 class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900">
          <%= tabler_icon("lifebuoy", classes: "h-6 w-6 text-indigo-600") %>
          <span>Help & Documentation</span>
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-500">A guided overview of what each part of the app does and when to use it.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  <% end %>

  <section class="rounded-xl border border-indigo-100 bg-indigo-50 p-5 shadow-sm">
    <div class="flex flex-wrap items-start gap-3">
      <div class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-indigo-600 text-white">
        <%= tabler_icon("help", classes: "ta-panel-icon") %>
      </div>
      <div class="flex-1 min-w-0">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">Start here</h3>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">The app works best in a simple order: set up your accounts, save your recurring transactions, create the month, then keep it updated as real life happens.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-4 grid gap-3 md:grid-cols-4">
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-indigo-100 bg-white/80 p-3">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-indigo-500">1. Accounts</p>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">Add checking, savings, cards, and other balances you want to track.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-indigo-100 bg-white/80 p-3">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-indigo-500">2. Recurring</p>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">Save paychecks, bills, subscriptions, and card payments as recurring transactions.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-indigo-100 bg-white/80 p-3">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-indigo-500">3. Start the month</p>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">Create or clone a month, then pull those recurring transactions into it from Plan and Edit.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-indigo-100 bg-white/80 p-3">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-indigo-500">4. Adjust as you go</p>
        <p class="mt-1 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">Add one-offs, import activity, update actuals, and mark items paid.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
      <a href="#dashboard" class="rounded-full border border-indigo-200 bg-white px-3 py-1.5 text-sm font-medium text-indigo-700 hover:bg-indigo-100">Dashboard</a>
      <a href="#months" class="rounded-full border border-indigo-200 bg-white px-3 py-1.5 text-sm font-medium text-indigo-700 hover:bg-indigo-100">Months</a>
      <a href="#entries" class="rounded-full border border-indigo-200 bg-white px-3 py-1.5 text-sm font-medium text-indigo-700 hover:bg-indigo-100">Plan and Edit</a>
      <a href="#templates" class="rounded-full border border-indigo-200 bg-white px-3 py-1.5 text-sm font-medium text-indigo-700 hover:bg-indigo-100">Recurring</a>
      <a href="#review" class="rounded-full border border-indigo-200 bg-white px-3 py-1.5 text-sm font-medium text-indigo-700 hover:bg-indigo-100">Review</a>
      <%= link_to help_releases_path, class: "rounded-full border border-indigo-200 bg-white px-3 py-1.5 text-sm font-medium text-indigo-700 hover:bg-indigo-100" do %>
        Release notes
      <% end %>
      <%= link_to hosted_documentation_url, class: "rounded-full border border-indigo-200 bg-white px-3 py-1.5 text-sm font-medium text-indigo-700 hover:bg-indigo-100", target: "_blank", rel: "noopener" do %>
        Full web docs
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="grid gap-6 xl:grid-cols-[1.5fr,1fr]">
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <section id="dashboard" class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">
          <%= tabler_icon("calendar-month", classes: "h-5 w-5 text-indigo-600") %>
          <span>Home and Months</span>
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">Home is a lightweight Overview page. The Months screen is where existing months, imports, and month-related actions now live.</p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">
          <li><strong class="text-slate-900">Use Home as a landing page:</strong> the overview is meant to point you toward the next setup step or the month that most needs attention.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-slate-900">Add accounts first:</strong> linked accounts show up in monthly views, make account filters more useful, and keep account balance rollups accurate.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-slate-900">Save recurring transactions before the first month:</strong> doing that makes Plan and Edit much faster once the month exists.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-slate-900">Use Months to open a month fast:</strong> jump back into an active month or revisit an older one.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-slate-900">Use Months for quick import:</strong> drag and drop a CSV there when you want to populate a month faster.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="months" class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">
          <%= tabler_icon("copy", classes: "h-5 w-5 text-indigo-600") %>
          <span>Creating and cloning months</span>
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">Each month is its own working budget. Most people set up recurring transactions first, then use the month wizard to start fresh or clone a previous month and pull them into the new month.</p>
        <div class="mt-4 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-4">
            <h4 class="font-medium text-slate-900">Start fresh</h4>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">Best when income, notes, or the overall budget structure is changing. You manually enter the month basics and then use Plan and Edit to pull in the recurring items you want.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-4">
            <h4 class="font-medium text-slate-900">Clone an existing month</h4>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">Best when the next month will mostly follow the same pattern. The app copies entries forward, clears actual amounts, resets them to planned, and chooses the next available month automatically.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="entries" class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">
          <%= tabler_icon("list", classes: "h-5 w-5 text-indigo-600") %>
          <span>Adding and managing entries</span>
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">Entries are the building blocks of each month. They represent income, bills, spending, debt payments, and manual adjustments after your recurring transaction structure is in place.</p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">
          <li><strong class="text-slate-900">Manual entry form:</strong> useful for quick edits and one-off transactions that appear after the month has already been set up.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-slate-900">Entry wizard:</strong> useful when you want a more guided flow through the fields and may want to save the result as a recurring transaction.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-slate-900">CSV import:</strong> useful when you already have transaction data outside the app and want to avoid retyping it.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-slate-900">Planned vs actual amounts:</strong> planned helps with forecasting, actual helps track what really happened.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-slate-900">Status:</strong> use planned, paid, and other statuses to track progress through the month, and mark items paid as they clear.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-slate-900">Recurring auto-marking:</strong> some recurring-generated entries can automatically mark themselves paid when they become due.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="templates" class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">
          <%= tabler_icon("repeat", classes: "h-5 w-5 text-emerald-600") %>
          <span>Recurring Transactions</span>
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">Add recurring transactions for the repeating monthly items you expect so you do not have to rebuild the same month from scratch. This is where you store paychecks, bills, subscriptions, payment plans, and card payments before you create the month.</p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">
          <li><strong class="text-slate-900">Save the recurring items you expect:</strong> store income, bills, debt payments, subscriptions, and other repeating activity once, then pull them into future months from Plan and Edit.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-slate-900">Connect recurring transactions to the right accounts:</strong> link each recurring item to the account it affects so the month is easier to scan and account balances stay more useful.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-slate-900">For credit cards, connect both sides of the payment:</strong> link the card account that is being paid down and the checking or cash account that will make the payment.</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="mt-4 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-200 p-4">
            <h4 class="font-medium text-slate-900">Paycheck schedules</h4>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">For recurring income sources like payroll or other regular deposits.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-200 p-4">
            <h4 class="font-medium text-slate-900">Subscriptions</h4>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">For recurring monthly services such as streaming, mobile plans, and software.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-200 p-4">
            <h4 class="font-medium text-slate-900">Monthly bills</h4>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">For fixed or variable bills that return every month, such as rent, utilities, or car payments.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-200 p-4">
            <h4 class="font-medium text-slate-900">Payment plans</h4>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">For balances paid down over time, such as installment plans or tax plans.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-200 p-4 md:col-span-2">
            <h4 class="font-medium text-slate-900">Credit cards</h4>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">For minimum-payment, due-day, and priority settings used by the card estimate feature when there is leftover cash to allocate.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="review" class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">
          <%= tabler_icon("chart-pie", classes: "h-5 w-5 text-indigo-600") %>
          <span>Reviewing a month</span>
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">Once entries are in place, the app gives several ways to review and manage the month while you keep adjusting amounts, adding one-offs, and marking activity paid.</p>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-4">
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-4">
            <h4 class="font-medium text-slate-900">Budget view</h4>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">Use this for a grouped, list-style, or calendar view with totals, filters, and quick scanning across the month.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-4">
            <h4 class="font-medium text-slate-900">Breakdown view</h4>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">Use this when you want the charts, monthly flow graph, and visual budget breakdown without mixing them into the main budget workflow.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-4">
            <h4 class="font-medium text-slate-900">Calendar (within Budget)</h4>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">Switch to the Calendar toggle in the Budget view when dates matter most and you want to see activity distributed across the month.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-4">
            <h4 class="font-medium text-slate-900">Plan and Edit view</h4>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">Use this to import recurring transactions, create one-off entries manually, and manage the month list in one place.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <section class="rounded-xl border border-emerald-100 bg-emerald-50 p-5 shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">
          <%= tabler_icon("sparkles", classes: "h-5 w-5 text-emerald-600") %>
          <span>Release notes</span>
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">Product updates now live on their own page so you can review what changed without mixing release history into the main help guide.</p>
        <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
          <%= link_to help_releases_path, class: "fb-btn-primary ta-action-btn" do %>
            <%= tabler_icon("sparkles", classes: "ta-action-icon") %>
            <span>Open release notes</span>
          <% end %>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">
          <%= tabler_icon("sparkles", classes: "h-5 w-5 text-indigo-600") %>
          <span>Helpful app behaviors</span>
        </h3>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">
          <li><strong class="text-slate-900">Reason-based pills:</strong> filters are based on the values that actually exist in the current month, making focused review easier.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-slate-900">Recurring actions:</strong> the Plan and Edit tab includes actions for adding paychecks, subscriptions, bills, and plans from saved recurring transactions.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-slate-900">Auto-completion:</strong> recurring-generated entries can automatically mark themselves paid when they become due.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-slate-900">Card payment estimates:</strong> the app creates minimum-payment entries for active cards and uses leftover cash to increase those estimates when the month has room.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-slate-900">Recurring safeguards:</strong> older months that look complete hide recurring action buttons to reduce accidental duplication.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-slate-900">Private account data:</strong> each signed-in user only sees their own months, entries, imports, and recurring transactions.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">
          <%= tabler_icon("check-circle", classes: "h-5 w-5 text-emerald-600") %>
          <span>Recommended first steps</span>
        </h3>
        <ol class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">
          <li>1. Add your main accounts first and record snapshots if you want a balance starting point.</li>
          <li>2. Add recurring transactions for the incoming and outgoing activity you expect.</li>
          <li>3. Create a month or clone the most recent one.</li>
          <li>4. Open Plan and Edit and pull those recurring transactions into the month.</li>
          <li>5. Import a CSV or add one-off items manually as the real month unfolds.</li>
          <li>6. Mark items paid, update actual amounts, and review the month in Budget, Breakdown, Calendar, and Plan and Edit.</li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <section class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">
          <%= tabler_icon("arrow-right", classes: "h-5 w-5 text-indigo-600") %>
          <span>Where to go next</span>
        </h3>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm">
          <%= link_to budget_months_path, class: "flex items-center justify-between rounded-lg border border-slate-200 px-3 py-2 text-slate-700 transition hover:border-indigo-200 hover:bg-indigo-50 hover:text-indigo-700" do %>
            <span>Go to Months</span>
            <%= tabler_icon("arrow-right", classes: "ta-action-icon") %>
          <% end %>
          <%= link_to accounts_path, class: "flex items-center justify-between rounded-lg border border-slate-200 px-3 py-2 text-slate-700 transition hover:border-indigo-200 hover:bg-indigo-50 hover:text-indigo-700" do %>
            <span>Set up Accounts</span>
            <%= tabler_icon("arrow-right", classes: "ta-action-icon") %>
          <% end %>
          <%= link_to planning_templates_path, class: "flex items-center justify-between rounded-lg border border-slate-200 px-3 py-2 text-slate-700 transition hover:border-indigo-200 hover:bg-indigo-50 hover:text-indigo-700" do %>
            <span>Open Recurring</span>
            <%= tabler_icon("arrow-right", classes: "ta-action-icon") %>
          <% end %>
          <%= link_to new_budget_month_path, class: "flex items-center justify-between rounded-lg border border-slate-200 px-3 py-2 text-slate-700 transition hover:border-indigo-200 hover:bg-indigo-50 hover:text-indigo-700" do %>
            <span>Create a New Month</span>
            <%= tabler_icon("arrow-right", classes: "ta-action-icon") %>
          <% end %>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
